---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL || '/';
const withBase = (path: string) =>
  base === '/' ? path : base.replace(/\/$/, '') + path;
---

<BaseLayout title="Database Development" sideBarActiveItemID="projects">
  <article class="prose max-w-none">
    <div class="flex flex-row items-center gap-4 mb-6">
      <img
        src={withBase('/logos/cornell-logo.png')}
        alt="Cornell University logo"
        class="h-24 w-auto"   /* identical visual height to AWS */
        loading="lazy"
      />
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold leading-tight mt-4">
        Database Development (Java)
      </h1>
    </div>

    <p class="text-base leading-relaxed">
      Architected and deployed a SQL-style database managing 100K+ records, implementing core relational operators
      and a dynamic query planner that selects efficient algorithms across different dataset sizes.
    </p>

    <section class="mt-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">What I built</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc ml-6 space-y-2">
        <li>
          Implemented core relational operators (selection, projection, joins) on top of a custom Java storage layer.
        </li>
        <li>
          Built and compared tuple nested loop join and block nested loop join, benchmarking their performance across
          varying table sizes and join selectivities.
        </li>
        <li>
          Designed basic indexing and statistics collection to speed up lookups and inform query-planning decisions.
        </li>
        <li>
          Developed a query planner that chooses join algorithms and access paths based on dataset size and available
          resources, automatically adapting from small (1K) to large (100K+) tables.
        </li>
        <li>
          Added a test harness and integration tests to validate correctness across edge cases and prevent regressions
          as new operators were added.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Skills I strengthened</h2>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
        <span class="badge badge-outline">Relational Database Design</span>
        <span class="badge badge-outline">Query Optimization</span>
        <span class="badge badge-outline">Join Algorithm Implementation</span>
        <span class="badge badge-outline">Indexing &amp; Data Structures</span>
        <span class="badge badge-outline">Performance Profiling</span>
        <span class="badge badge-outline">Java Backend Development</span>
      </div>
      <p class="mt-4">
        This project gave me hands-on experience with how databases actually execute queries under the hoodâ€”how join
        algorithms behave at different scales, how indexing and statistics influence performance, and how a query
        planner can turn a declarative SQL request into an efficient execution plan.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
